WEBVTT

00:01.293 --> 00:03.452
Well, since cousin Amanda's
visiting for the weekend,

00:03.629 --> 00:06.121
I thought I'd get her a little present.

00:07.382 --> 00:09.127
That's a thoughtful gift for all of us.

00:09.301 --> 00:11.176
Now, now, she's family.

00:11.345 --> 00:12.923
We should welcome her
with open arms.

00:14.556 --> 00:17.926
If she tries anything, we have
an electric cage in the basement.

00:18.894 --> 00:20.519
She's back.

00:22.481 --> 00:25.767
Hi, everybody.
It's so good to see you.

00:26.902 --> 00:29.738
Get your pointer fingers up in the air
where I can see them.

00:30.531 --> 00:32.156
Enough, Barney Fife.

00:32.323 --> 00:34.401
Sabrina,
I don't blame you for being suspicious.

00:34.576 --> 00:36.736
My behaviour in past
may have been a little bratty.

00:36.912 --> 00:38.158
Yeah, you were a little bratty

00:38.330 --> 00:40.371
and Nazi Germany
was a little aggressive.

00:40.541 --> 00:41.573
But I've grown up.

00:41.750 --> 00:43.543
I'm now a teenage witch,
just like you.

00:45.379 --> 00:47.622
I have to admit,
she does seem more mature.

00:49.550 --> 00:53.798
[SINGING]
<i>Call me irresponsible</i>

00:53.971 --> 00:55.929
Okay, there's mature
and there's scary.

00:56.098 --> 00:58.851
<i>Unreliable</i>

00:59.017 --> 01:05.816
<i>Throw in undependable too</i>

01:07.000 --> 01:13.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:39.558 --> 01:42.132
- Rock, paper, scissors.
- Rock, paper, scissors.

01:43.645 --> 01:46.054
Rock breaks scissors. You lose.

01:46.607 --> 01:49.977
Finally, for once in my life, you lose.

01:50.152 --> 01:51.232
Fine.

01:51.403 --> 01:52.685
I'll be the one to tell Sabrina

01:52.863 --> 01:55.022
that she has to stay with Amanda
while we're at work.

01:58.452 --> 01:59.947
I'll get the chips. You go get CDs.

02:00.120 --> 02:01.402
Got it.

02:04.625 --> 02:08.669
And as per our agreement,
since I'm giving Sabrina the bad news,

02:08.836 --> 02:10.582
you have to scrub all the pots.

02:13.634 --> 02:15.841
Zelda,
you wanna help me dust the clocks?

02:16.011 --> 02:20.010
No, remember, you were going to be
in the front minding the store

02:20.182 --> 02:23.433
and I was going to be in the back
working, alone.

02:23.602 --> 02:25.346
Oh, yeah.

02:28.732 --> 02:30.477
Zelda, I made some tea.
Do you want some?

02:30.651 --> 02:34.649
No, I'm working, alone.

02:37.115 --> 02:40.283
You probably didn't know
it was jasmine.

02:42.287 --> 02:44.080
[GURGLING]

02:46.792 --> 02:48.073
[GURGLING]

02:48.252 --> 02:49.663
Stop it.

02:49.878 --> 02:50.910
[BOOM]

02:51.088 --> 02:52.500
Company.

02:53.298 --> 02:55.672
I'm never gonna get anything done.

02:55.843 --> 02:58.299
Nice bottle.

02:58.470 --> 02:59.716
Oh, look, there's a message.

02:59.888 --> 03:02.843
Probably some shipwrecked soul
searching for their lost love.

03:03.016 --> 03:05.306
"Please recycle."

03:11.149 --> 03:14.436
I wish bottles came
with a vortex warning.

03:14.611 --> 03:16.404
A genie must have lived here.

03:16.572 --> 03:17.853
Or Luther Vandross.

03:18.031 --> 03:21.864
This place is charming
and so private.

03:22.035 --> 03:23.744
I could make this my office.

03:23.912 --> 03:27.115
Let's get out of here.
It smells like stinky genie feet.

03:27.291 --> 03:28.406
Oh, you know what?

03:28.584 --> 03:31.420
I bet we have to flip this switch
to get out.

03:34.798 --> 03:38.049
Wow. Did you use a lot of hairspray
this morning?

03:38.218 --> 03:40.011
A little.

03:40.888 --> 03:43.261
Okay, Sabrina, here's your usual,

03:43.432 --> 03:47.300
and, Amanda, your Colombian blend,
black, just like you ordered.

03:47.477 --> 03:48.558
Thank you, Josh.

03:50.314 --> 03:52.224
Mmm. My first sip of coffee.

03:55.068 --> 03:57.109
And my last.

03:57.279 --> 03:58.395
Hey, Sabrina.

03:58.572 --> 04:00.779
Oh, hey,
you remember my cousin Amanda?

04:00.949 --> 04:03.868
I sure do.
You're such a young lady now.

04:04.036 --> 04:06.610
I remember
when you were yay high.

04:07.206 --> 04:09.958
Why am I talking like my uncle Jay?

04:10.834 --> 04:11.950
Dear diary,

04:12.127 --> 04:15.378
I had my first cup of coffee
and I met Sabrina's boss, Josh.

04:15.547 --> 04:18.964
Is he cute or what?
Give me an exclamation point there.

04:19.176 --> 04:20.552
SORECORN:
Mm.

04:20.719 --> 04:23.555
- And then later, Harvey showed up.
SABRINA: Amanda?

04:23.722 --> 04:25.716
- I'll finish later, Miss Sorecorn.
- Yes, ma'am.

04:25.891 --> 04:29.012
And I'll dot the I's with little hearts,
as per usual.

04:29.603 --> 04:31.395
- Your mom's on the phone.
- Thanks.

04:31.563 --> 04:32.809
Oh, and by the end of the day,

04:32.981 --> 04:34.809
I need a recount
on my remaining Red Hots.

04:34.983 --> 04:36.728
Yes, ma'am.

04:38.362 --> 04:40.901
Amanda loves Josh.

04:41.073 --> 04:43.742
I love when the eavesdropping
comes to me.

04:43.909 --> 04:46.235
Well, he was being
awfully nice to her.

04:46.411 --> 04:47.907
So Amanda has a crush on Josh,
huh?

04:48.080 --> 04:49.195
Great reaction.

04:49.373 --> 04:52.161
I thought I'd at least get
a girlish squeal out of you.

04:52.417 --> 04:53.533
[SQUEALS]

04:53.710 --> 04:55.953
I know that was sarcastic,
but thank you.

04:57.714 --> 05:01.001
Attention, everyone,
this is my new office.

05:01.176 --> 05:03.846
And when the lid is on,
I am not to be disturbed.

05:04.012 --> 05:06.765
If you get tired of it,
you can return it and get a nickel back.

05:06.932 --> 05:09.389
Be careful with that.

05:09.726 --> 05:13.143
You know, it's so inspiring to have
a private place to do one's work.

05:13.313 --> 05:16.268
To me, this will be
like Hemingway's Key West study.

05:16.441 --> 05:19.016
- But you're not a writer.
- Like Monet's Giverny.

05:19.194 --> 05:21.484
- You're not an artist.
- I just wanna be alone, okay?

05:21.655 --> 05:22.984
You're not Garbo either.

05:23.782 --> 05:25.408
Don't worry about me bothering you.

05:25.576 --> 05:27.320
I'll be antiquing in the 16th century.

05:27.494 --> 05:29.867
Thirteenth-century stuff
was much cheaper then.

05:30.038 --> 05:32.791
I just want everyone clear,
this bottle is off-limits.

05:32.958 --> 05:34.038
Please tell Amanda.

05:34.209 --> 05:38.078
Speaking of Amanda, it turns out
she has a little crush on Josh.

05:38.255 --> 05:41.292
Amanda likes an older man?
That is so cute.

05:41.466 --> 05:43.294
Just like when I had it bad
for Sean Connery.

05:43.468 --> 05:45.961
You are several centuries
older than Sean Connery.

05:46.138 --> 05:48.131
I know that.
I just like talking about him.

05:48.807 --> 05:52.391
Sabrina, I think it's best
not to encourage this crush on Josh.

05:52.561 --> 05:54.970
I know. That's why we're not
going back to the coffeehouse.

05:55.147 --> 05:57.473
Harvey's coming here, Amanda
will have to hang out with us

05:57.649 --> 05:59.939
and act like a normal teenager.

06:01.153 --> 06:02.814
Amanda needs toner.

06:04.531 --> 06:06.110
I think I'll put you outside

06:06.283 --> 06:08.360
so the sun can shine
through the glass.

06:08.535 --> 06:11.241
I just love natural light.

06:15.792 --> 06:17.501
Oh, finally.

06:17.669 --> 06:20.161
I can get some work done.

06:23.800 --> 06:27.550
Oh, I just love early-century genie.

06:30.641 --> 06:34.058
Who says you can't find happiness
at the bottom of a bottle?

06:34.228 --> 06:36.554
Sealed with a kiss.

06:37.689 --> 06:40.608
Oh, who's the letter for?
Someone you have a crush on?

06:40.776 --> 06:43.944
- No, it's for my mom.
- Oh, really?

06:44.112 --> 06:47.981
Yeah, well, my mom likes
Passion Fruity Girl too.

06:49.284 --> 06:51.242
Zellie, I'm back from antiquing.

06:51.411 --> 06:54.164
I didn't find any clocks,
but I got a great deal on a plough.

06:54.331 --> 06:55.447
Go away.

06:59.419 --> 07:01.247
What are you doing?

07:01.797 --> 07:03.422
And what's with the outfit?

07:03.590 --> 07:06.628
I specifically told you
I did not wanna be disturbed.

07:06.802 --> 07:09.970
- You've got a guy in here, don't you?
- Go away.

07:10.138 --> 07:12.049
Hey,
I bet you haven't tried these switches.

07:13.183 --> 07:15.426
- Cool.
- Turn it off.

07:16.019 --> 07:17.183
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYS]

07:17.354 --> 07:18.470
Oh, I love this song.

07:18.647 --> 07:20.724
Let me do it.

07:21.817 --> 07:22.980
[POWER TURNS OFF]

07:23.151 --> 07:24.944
Uh-oh. Looks like you broke
your little bottle.

07:25.112 --> 07:26.773
See you.

07:30.576 --> 07:33.032
The exit switch isn't working.
We're trapped.

07:33.203 --> 07:35.909
And I wanna go play
with my new plough.

07:36.081 --> 07:37.576
Right foot, yellow.

07:37.749 --> 07:39.375
Right hand, ow!

07:39.543 --> 07:41.371
[PHONE RINGING]

07:41.837 --> 07:43.914
Okay, back.

07:44.089 --> 07:45.584
Hello?

07:45.757 --> 07:47.798
Really? Yeah, I'll be right there.

07:49.219 --> 07:51.676
Okay, Josh is swamped.

07:51.847 --> 07:53.805
I gotta go to work. Sorry.

07:53.974 --> 07:55.849
- No problem.
- Send Josh my regards.

07:56.018 --> 07:57.098
Of course.

07:57.269 --> 08:00.472
Well, you two
just make yourselves comfortable.

08:03.734 --> 08:05.562
Let's play something
a little less painful.

08:06.320 --> 08:08.230
How about jousting?

08:09.239 --> 08:11.945
Handy Dandy brush man.

08:13.452 --> 08:14.651
Ooh.

08:14.828 --> 08:17.403
That's a good-looking bottle.

08:17.581 --> 08:18.827
I'll bet these would sell.

08:21.877 --> 08:23.206
A mortal got sucked in.

08:23.378 --> 08:25.206
Even worse, a salesman.

08:25.380 --> 08:27.208
How do we explain this?

08:27.382 --> 08:28.794
Handy Dandy brush man.

08:30.177 --> 08:33.796
Tired of throwing money away
on costly combs and brushes?

08:33.972 --> 08:36.215
Yes, it's the comb-brush.

08:36.390 --> 08:37.506
Explain what?

08:38.018 --> 08:40.344
Okay, get ready to tip your cups
and empty your bladders.

08:40.520 --> 08:42.727
The brewmaster general is here.

08:43.815 --> 08:46.272
Hello? Josh?

08:46.443 --> 08:50.027
Sabrina,
so good of you to rush down.

08:51.073 --> 08:54.240
Let's forget the charade. I love you.

08:54.409 --> 08:56.070
Okay, Josh,
I knew you kind of liked me,

08:56.245 --> 08:58.404
but had no idea your feelings
would cause a breakdown.

08:58.580 --> 09:00.823
And an ascot.

09:00.999 --> 09:03.752
Oh, a chocolate soufflÃ©.

09:03.919 --> 09:06.956
You know, you really raised the bar
on snack time.

09:07.130 --> 09:09.041
Harvey, this is for you.

09:09.216 --> 09:11.091
Thanks, Amanda.

09:11.260 --> 09:13.716
Hm. Smells like my mom's bridge club.

09:22.855 --> 09:25.097
HARVEY: <i>Amanda,
are you sure this letter is for me?</i>

09:26.775 --> 09:29.730
Of course it is. I like you, Harvey.

09:29.903 --> 09:30.686
Huh?

09:30.863 --> 09:34.197
Sabrina,
you're positively bewitching.

09:34.366 --> 09:36.027
I'm under your spell.

09:36.201 --> 09:39.073
There's a spell going on here,
but it's not mine.

09:41.081 --> 09:42.363
[PHONE RINGS]

09:42.541 --> 09:43.705
Help. I mean, hello?

09:43.876 --> 09:45.953
Sabrina, Amanda doesn't like Josh.

09:46.128 --> 09:47.623
She likes Harvey.

09:47.796 --> 09:49.790
- Harvey?
- Call me Josh.

09:49.965 --> 09:51.164
Okay, it's all clear now.

09:51.341 --> 09:52.837
Amanda wanted to be alone
with Harvey,

09:53.010 --> 09:54.422
so she put this spell on Josh.

09:54.595 --> 09:56.968
For the simple days
when she could turn me into a doll.

09:58.140 --> 09:59.600
Wait, don't rush off.

09:59.766 --> 10:01.559
There's so much
we haven't talked about.

10:02.311 --> 10:03.510
Like kissing.

10:05.522 --> 10:08.228
Don't be afraid to swoon,
I'll be here to catch you.

10:08.901 --> 10:10.775
Okay, he's under a cad spell.

10:10.944 --> 10:12.060
I hate to do this.

10:12.237 --> 10:14.278
You cad.

10:16.533 --> 10:19.784
I wasn't just blurting out
my true feelings for you, was I?

10:19.953 --> 10:22.362
Oh, were you blurting?
I wasn't paying attention.

10:22.539 --> 10:24.414
Amanda, this is really flattering,

10:24.583 --> 10:27.455
but Sabrina and I
are sort of going together.

10:27.628 --> 10:29.835
And besides,
I'm way too old for you.

10:30.005 --> 10:31.381
I understand, Harvey.

10:32.007 --> 10:33.917
But I like the way
you've made your vowels pink

10:34.092 --> 10:35.422
and your consonants green.

10:35.594 --> 10:37.884
I guess this really
isn't the time or place for us.

10:38.055 --> 10:40.298
But I know what is.

10:44.228 --> 10:46.268
Harvey's all mine on Cloud 9.

10:50.943 --> 10:52.106
Amanda.

10:52.277 --> 10:53.986
Bring my boyfriend back.

10:54.154 --> 10:55.400
You're gonna pay for this.

10:55.572 --> 10:58.823
Well, you really told the ceiling off.

11:04.540 --> 11:06.165
Salem,
you have to help me find Harvey.

11:06.333 --> 11:10.747
Well, he's not in the candy dish.
I'm stumped.

11:10.921 --> 11:12.796
Forget it. I'll just go ask Aunt Hilda.

11:12.965 --> 11:14.709
Oh, she's shopping
in another century.

11:14.883 --> 11:17.589
Aunt Zelda will be furious
if I try to disturb her in her bottle.

11:17.761 --> 11:19.885
- Sabrina.
- Sabrina.

11:20.055 --> 11:22.464
- Sabrina.
- Sabrina.

11:22.641 --> 11:24.136
There's gotta be a spell
to find Harvey.

11:24.309 --> 11:27.726
Oh, oh, oh! Mr. Kotter, I know one.

11:27.896 --> 11:30.104
Can I say the spell
and you do the zapping?

11:30.274 --> 11:32.148
- Just hurry.
- Ahem.

11:32.317 --> 11:36.363
<i>Where'd they go, you do the math
Help me follow Harvey's path</i>

11:36.530 --> 11:37.694
That was fun.

11:39.575 --> 11:43.739
Meet Sherlock Bones.
If he can't find him, nobody can.

11:43.912 --> 11:45.407
Sherlock, okay,
Harvey was last seen--

11:45.581 --> 11:48.452
He's a dog. He can't talk.

11:49.710 --> 11:52.665
Just give him something of Harvey's
so he can pick up the scent.

11:52.838 --> 11:54.878
Hey, here's Harvey's jacket. Here.

11:55.048 --> 11:58.216
Maybe this will help you track his trail!

12:04.016 --> 12:05.475
Oh, no.

12:05.642 --> 12:07.683
Storage? He's in here?

12:07.853 --> 12:09.562
Oh, did Amanda stuff him in a box?

12:09.771 --> 12:11.599
[DOG WHIMPERS]

12:15.110 --> 12:17.779
No wonder genies have to turn
into smoke to get out of these.

12:17.946 --> 12:20.236
This seal is really tight.

12:20.407 --> 12:23.076
Zellie, try this brush.
It makes your hair smell like grape.

12:25.454 --> 12:28.622
Don't worry, someone's gonna
come along and get us out of here.

12:28.790 --> 12:31.579
I don't want to get us out of here,
I want to get you out of here.

12:35.964 --> 12:37.673
Cool hideout.

12:37.841 --> 12:40.380
You've obviously got bucks.

12:40.552 --> 12:43.340
How many boxes of brittle
can we sign you up for?

12:43.514 --> 12:46.765
I just want to be alone.

12:47.184 --> 12:48.465
What kind of brittle?

12:50.437 --> 12:52.347
They're here? Cloud 9?

12:54.191 --> 12:55.734
[DOG WHIMPERS]

12:56.652 --> 12:57.933
Hey, where are you--?

12:58.111 --> 13:00.686
Oh, yeah, you're all work
until you see a squirrel.

13:01.448 --> 13:03.857
Why would Amanda
bring Harvey here?

13:04.409 --> 13:07.613
So you really like being with me,
don't you, Harvey?

13:07.788 --> 13:09.865
Well, I'm on Cloud 9.

13:10.040 --> 13:12.081
I like everything on Cloud 9.

13:12.251 --> 13:13.627
Why, you little home wrecker.

13:13.794 --> 13:15.669
Hey, you, get off of my cloud.

13:15.838 --> 13:17.796
I can't believe you tried to steal
my boyfriend.

13:17.965 --> 13:19.294
He's not your boyfriend anymore.

13:19.466 --> 13:21.294
- He's mine.
- No, he's mine.

13:21.468 --> 13:23.261
He's mine.

13:24.847 --> 13:27.220
HARVEY:
Wow. I'm flying.

13:27.391 --> 13:28.506
[THUMP]

13:28.684 --> 13:29.965
You broke my boyfriend.

13:30.143 --> 13:31.769
I didn't break your boyfriend.

13:31.937 --> 13:34.096
I broke my boyfriend.

13:35.482 --> 13:39.528
- Thank you for saving my boyfriend.
- For the last time, he's my--

13:40.112 --> 13:41.524
You know what?

13:41.697 --> 13:43.607
I give up, Harvey's yours.

13:44.116 --> 13:46.524
That means you're gonna have
to sign some release forms.

13:46.702 --> 13:49.657
Today a medical release form,
tomorrow a marriage licence.

13:49.830 --> 13:52.583
Be sure to let me know
where you're registered.

13:58.213 --> 14:01.299
When I ask for a wheelchair,
everyone says no.

14:01.466 --> 14:03.709
I gotta get Harvey out of harm's way.

14:03.886 --> 14:04.966
<i>Put Harvey in his own bed</i>

14:05.137 --> 14:07.012
<i>With none of these happenings
In his head</i>

14:08.974 --> 14:10.517
Weird.

14:10.684 --> 14:13.805
I haven't taken a nap in years.

14:16.398 --> 14:18.143
And I've got cloud in my hair.

14:18.317 --> 14:21.484
I've gotta find a way to stop
Amanda's infatuation with Harvey.

14:21.653 --> 14:24.739
So we're just not gonna talk
about my wheelchair?

14:24.907 --> 14:27.743
AMANDA: I'll get you, Sabrina,
and your little kitty too.

14:27.910 --> 14:29.488
[AMANDA LAUGHS]

14:31.538 --> 14:33.033
AMANDA:
I'm burning mad.

14:37.085 --> 14:39.126
Well, the queen of property damage
has arrived.

14:39.296 --> 14:40.577
Where did you hide my Harvey?

14:40.756 --> 14:43.248
You can have Harvey.
Just don't hurt me.

14:43.425 --> 14:44.457
[SOBS]

14:44.635 --> 14:45.916
What Salem's trying to say is,

14:46.094 --> 14:48.587
why don't we be mature about this
and discuss it rationally?

14:48.764 --> 14:50.757
I'll tear this room apart
until I find him.

14:50.933 --> 14:52.392
Interesting take on rational.

14:52.976 --> 14:54.602
Freeze.

15:02.361 --> 15:04.319
Talk about your cool cat.

15:04.488 --> 15:05.687
Sorry.

15:06.448 --> 15:09.735
I should do some early
Christmas shopping.

15:12.663 --> 15:15.332
Can't you people call during dinner
like everyone else?

15:15.499 --> 15:16.531
[KNOCKING]

15:16.708 --> 15:18.536
Hilda, it's Dreama.

15:18.710 --> 15:19.826
She can zap us out.

15:20.671 --> 15:22.166
Are we talking
about the same Dreama?

15:22.339 --> 15:26.041
We're desperate.
Dreama, zap us out.

15:26.218 --> 15:28.591
- But don't open the lid.
- What did you say?

15:31.598 --> 15:33.343
Zelda,
get your hands off of her throat.

15:33.559 --> 15:35.018
[SHIVERING]

15:35.185 --> 15:38.104
I've lost all feeling in my tail.

15:38.939 --> 15:41.894
I've gotta stop Amanda's infatuation
before she finds Harvey.

15:42.067 --> 15:43.859
There's nothing
under crush, puppy love,

15:44.027 --> 15:45.772
or psychotic preteen
lacking scruples

15:45.946 --> 15:47.489
or any sense of morality.

15:47.656 --> 15:50.528
Wagging that appendage
was my only creative outlet.

15:50.701 --> 15:53.240
- Oh, what will I do?
- Help me find a spell.

15:53.412 --> 15:54.907
Look under "desire."

15:56.790 --> 15:58.583
Oh! You're back.

15:59.293 --> 16:00.492
Whip it, tiger.

16:00.669 --> 16:04.750
Here's something. Hopefully
this will help kill Amanda's desire.

16:07.509 --> 16:10.215
Hey, Sabrina!

16:10.387 --> 16:12.048
Hey, Sabrina!

16:14.558 --> 16:16.682
Stanley Kinkle-ski?

16:16.852 --> 16:18.477
Don't ever leave me, baby.

16:19.104 --> 16:21.892
Maybe I should have read
the fine print on that desire spell.

16:22.065 --> 16:26.396
SALEM: Sabrina, it looks like you did
a <i>Streetcar Named Desire</i> spell.

16:26.570 --> 16:28.113
Thank you.

16:28.280 --> 16:30.653
No one's made me dinner.

16:31.742 --> 16:33.901
I have to eat before I go bowling.

16:34.077 --> 16:37.032
Yeah, well,
the spell certainly killed desire, mine.

16:40.751 --> 16:43.420
How did I tear my T-shirt?

16:44.046 --> 16:47.630
Why did I dream
I was playing poker with Karl Malden?

16:52.054 --> 16:54.344
Oh, dang, I miss Stanley.

16:56.683 --> 16:59.804
Where's Harvey?
I've looked everywhere, even Iowa.

16:59.978 --> 17:01.059
You looked in the Midwest

17:01.230 --> 17:02.725
and you didn't even check
his bedroom?

17:02.898 --> 17:04.726
- Salem.
- Thanks for the tip.

17:08.028 --> 17:09.488
A concrete solution.

17:09.655 --> 17:12.692
This might be a good time
to throw her in the river.

17:17.954 --> 17:19.330
You're stepping on my foot.

17:19.498 --> 17:21.076
Excuse me.

17:21.250 --> 17:23.457
I feel like I'm in a bejewelled anthill.

17:23.627 --> 17:26.748
Hilda,
why did you have to come in here?

17:26.922 --> 17:29.165
Why couldn't you
just leave me alone?

17:29.341 --> 17:31.085
I was excited
about the plough I bought.

17:31.260 --> 17:32.755
That's not true.

17:32.928 --> 17:35.005
And it could have waited until later.

17:35.180 --> 17:37.423
Well, this is a conundrum, isn't it?

17:37.599 --> 17:40.886
And why is it that our entire lives,

17:41.061 --> 17:46.139
whenever I tried to find solitude
in my own room, tree house, pod,

17:46.316 --> 17:48.061
there you were? Why is that?

17:48.902 --> 17:50.528
Well, the only thing I can think of

17:50.696 --> 17:53.270
is that, a lot of the time
there's just the two of us,

17:53.448 --> 17:56.450
so that if you're alone,
that means I'm alone.

17:56.618 --> 17:59.537
And when I'm alone, I get lonely.

17:59.705 --> 18:01.414
Hilda, we've had a breakthrough.

18:02.124 --> 18:03.833
I understand you now.

18:04.001 --> 18:05.496
I want to be alone,

18:05.669 --> 18:09.288
but you have every right
not to be alone.

18:09.464 --> 18:12.383
Do me a favour, get a dog.

18:12.551 --> 18:14.841
That's a great idea.
We'll go to the pound together.

18:18.557 --> 18:19.637
I have to do something

18:19.808 --> 18:22.477
before Amanda pulls
an Incredible Hulk on that cement.

18:22.644 --> 18:24.768
I know I'm not supposed
to disturb Aunt Zelda but--

18:24.980 --> 18:26.060
[THUMPING]

18:26.231 --> 18:27.976
The monster's on the move.

18:31.028 --> 18:32.606
Go ahead, you big tattletale.

18:32.779 --> 18:35.698
I guess you're not mature enough
to handle this one on your own.

18:35.866 --> 18:39.117
I don't need any help.
I can solve this one all by myself.

18:39.953 --> 18:41.034
Salem, what do I do?

18:41.205 --> 18:44.788
Well, hiring a hit man
is prohibitively expensive.

18:45.417 --> 18:48.787
So I guess you could just wait for her
to outgrow this crush on Harvey.

18:48.962 --> 18:50.623
Why wait when one is a witch?

18:50.797 --> 18:52.791
I can use magic
to make her grow up.

19:03.727 --> 19:05.768
[SPEAKING INAUDIBLY]

19:29.545 --> 19:31.918
So now that you've blossomed,
are you any older and wiser?

19:32.089 --> 19:35.790
I sure am. Wise enough to know
I wanna stay a kid as long as I can.

19:35.968 --> 19:37.878
- Wonderful.
- Since I'm a kid,

19:38.053 --> 19:39.299
I don't need boyfriend.

19:39.471 --> 19:42.343
Perfect. I have finally done a spell
that turned out the way it should.

19:42.516 --> 19:46.467
And in the sprit of staying young,
I'm gonna cut your hair.

19:49.356 --> 19:51.433
See, perfect spell.

19:51.608 --> 19:53.269
I needed a new haircut.

19:53.443 --> 19:54.725
Aunt Zelda.

19:55.696 --> 19:56.859
Aunt Zelda.

19:57.030 --> 19:59.605
Am I the only one
who thinks we're running out of air?

19:59.783 --> 20:01.065
Sabrina's our only hope.

20:03.370 --> 20:04.782
Amanda's our only hope.

20:04.955 --> 20:07.114
AMANDA:
I'm going home.

20:07.541 --> 20:09.581
Like I said, Salem's our only hope.

20:09.793 --> 20:11.372
[SNORING]

20:15.716 --> 20:17.591
[YAWNING]

20:18.218 --> 20:21.588
Oh, nothing like a little catnap.

20:21.763 --> 20:23.841
Hey, where is everybody?
I'm hungry.

20:24.016 --> 20:26.223
Zelda, feed me.

20:27.603 --> 20:30.973
I will not be ignored.

20:34.067 --> 20:36.275
Well, Aunt Zelda,
I'm really sorry about your bottle,

20:36.445 --> 20:38.106
but I think
there's an empty can in trash.

20:38.280 --> 20:40.819
Yeah, too bad Salem
ruined your secret hideaway.

20:41.408 --> 20:45.407
Well, that is the one good thing
about being a witch.

20:45.996 --> 20:49.081
Everyone,
stay out of my tree house.

20:49.249 --> 20:51.124
Tree house?

20:55.339 --> 20:58.506
Well, it's getting late.
I'll walk you to your door.

20:58.675 --> 21:00.135
I had a really great time tonight.

21:00.302 --> 21:01.466
Me too.

21:01.637 --> 21:04.425
When I'm with you, Sabrina,
I'm on Cloud 9.

21:09.561 --> 21:10.677
Harvey, I have to tell you.

21:10.854 --> 21:13.477
I'm sorry, but I'm breaking up with you.
It's for the best.

21:18.111 --> 21:20.686
Sabrina, do you ever black out
and miss big parts of the day?

